Text:
you probably either have a self-signed certificate, or a chained certificate where some portion of the chain is not trusted.

You can import the certificate into your trust store see http://stackoverflow.com/questions/373295/digital-certificate-how-to-import-cer-file-in-to-truststore-file-using

Or you can ignore the problem as in this question http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2694281/ignore-certificate-errors-when-requesting-a-url-in-java
